effective date.
3
4
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
6 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.501 of Title 69, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 The bridge on State Highway 7 crossing over Little Beaver Creek
10 in Stephens County shall be designated as the "Captain Hunter Blaine
11 Memorial Bridge". The Department of Transportation shall cause
12 suitable permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on the
13 bridge.
14 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.502 of Title 69, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 The section of U.S. Highway 270 beginning at the intersection of
18 State Highway 2 extending west to the intersection of Shero-Austin
19 Road in Latimer County shall be designated as the "PFC William Tony
20 Brock Memorial Highway". The Department of Transportation shall
21 cause suitable permanent markers bearing that name to be placed on
22 the highway.
